# Canonicalize the project author identity.
#
# The author of this package is `Roma <RomaLytar@gmail.com>`. A few early
# bootstrap commits were accidentally authored under a different email
# inherited from the global git config; this file maps them to the correct
# personal identity.
#
# The raw commit data is left untouched — we never rewrite history on
# protected branches. Every git tool that respects mailmap (`git log`,
# `git blame`, `git shortlog`, GitHub UI, contributors page) will display
# the canonical name and email.
#
# Format:
#   Proper Name <proper@email> Commit Name <commit@email>

Roma <RomaLytar@gmail.com> Roman Lytar <rlytar@ed3p.com>
